description:
File: rust/lichen-ipv6/src/lib.rs:401-412

UdpHeader::from_bytes() parses the UDP length field but does not validate it against the actual buffer size. A malformed packet could claim a length larger than the actual data, leading callers to read past the end of valid data.

```rust
pub fn from_bytes(buf: &[u8]) -> Result<Self, Ipv6Error> {
    if buf.len() < UDP_HEADER_LEN {
        return Err(TooShort::new(UDP_HEADER_LEN, buf.len()).into());
    }
    // length field parsed but not validated
    Ok(Self {
        // ...
        length: ((buf[4] as u16) << 8) | (buf[5] as u16),
        // ...
    })
}
```

Callers using `header.length` to slice payload without additional bounds checking could read garbage or cause panics.

Consider adding validation or documenting that callers MUST validate the length field before using it.
